#include <sys/socket.h>  
int bind(int socket, struct sockaddr* addr, socklen_t addr_len);
  • Return value is 0 for success or -1 for error
  • addr contains information about this machines address, and which port to open
  • addr_len is needed because addr has variable size
  • Use getaddrinfo to fill in addr
